{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_fink_ver02/data/sn82016181/00529045633/1923110503/0180.xml":{"full_text":"TODAY\u2019S MARKET IN STOCKS, BONDS, COTTON, GRAINS\nSTOCKS\u2019 FORWARD\nMARCH RESUMED\nMovement Broadens After Sell\ning Is Absorbed\nBy Wall Street Journal\nNEW YORK\u2014Price movement in\ntoday\u2019s\nstock market adequately\ndemonstrated the staying qualities\nof the forces behind the\nrecent\nchange to strength.\nConstructive interests had awaited\nthe outcome of today\u2019s session in the\nbelief that the present week\u2019s start\nwould show whether last Wednes\nday\u2019s outburst of strength had rep\nresented a temporary improvement,\nor signalled a turning point.\nSelling Easily Absorbed\nThis test turned out satisfactorily\nin every respect from the bullish\nstandpoint. Week-end selling orders\nwere easily absorbed and prices be\ngan to move ahead again before the\nmorning was\nover.\nThis forward\nprocession showed definite broaden\ning tendencies.\nNew highs on the\nupswing were reached by Studeba\nker, Baldwin, General Electric, Du\nPont and most of the industrial\nleaders.\nPronounced strength was dis\nplayed by the rails and public utili\nwas\nties.\nEven the oils moved forward.\nNew Favorites\nFurther progress was made in the\nlast hour by the speculative leaders,\nbut prices held at the best on the\nmovement and new favorites were\nbrought to the front.\nIndustrial Alcohol made\na\nnew\nhigh on the movement at 553, Davi\nson Chemical at 5:\nPlayers at 60'4.\n8\nanti Famous\nThe public utilities were strong,\nled by Brooklyn-Edison, which sold\nat 112, up more than 4 from last\nweek's low.\nTechnical considerations governed\nthe early dealings.\nGeneral Electric maintained its\nrapid advance, reaching a new high\non the movement at 182%, but price\nchanges among the other industrial\nleaders were irregularly divided.\nThe rails were generally higher.\nSelling Absorbed\nStocks had to absorb considerable\nselling in the first hour, but the\nofferings in the general list were\ntaken at scant recessions from the\nmovement's best levels, while Du\nPont and a few other issues con\ntinued to move ahead.\nJudging from the industrial list\u2019s\naction, a business depression is not\nlikelv\nto materialize this\nwinter.\nThere are inquiries for close to 100,\n000 freight cars. American Can has\ncontracted for delivery of more tin\nplate than at any time in its history.\nThe chain stores and mail-order\nhouses are doing a record business.\nCopper Industry Picks Up\nAfter several dull weeks, the cop\nper industry has been revived with\nlarge sales.\nRailroads are making\nlarge contracts for steel rails. Build\ning contracts awarded in New York\nCity in October show a 61 per cent\nincrease over September and 33 over\nOctober, 1922.\nThe automobile industry is excep\nt ion ally\nactive, an indication that\ngasoline consumption will continue\nat a record rate.\nThere may not be\na business boom, but it looks as tho\nthe volume would keep labor fully\nemployed.\nOils Rebound\nSpeculative sentiment was encour\naged by the market's action in the\nlate morning. Not only did the gen\n\u201eeral list continue to hold well and\nspecial stocks like General Electric\nto move higher, but interest was re\nvived in a number of the backward\ngroups.\nOils like Texas Co., Marland and\nCosden, heavy in the early stages of\nlast week\u2019s recovery, scored substan\ntial rebounds.\nAttention was drawn by Stewart\nWarner\u2019s\nsharp upturn to 837s,\nagainst last week\u2019s low of 75'4, to\nthe fact that the company has no\noutstanding bonds, preferred stock\nor bank loans and has sufficient sur\nplus cash to pay a handsome extra\ndividend.\nHarvester Up 10\nInternational Harvester sold at\n763., up nearly 10 from last week\u2019s\nlow. The advance has not alone been\ndue to a turn for the better in the\ncompany\u2019s business.\nThe stock was\nsold heavily by a bear pool, which\nexperienced difficulty in buying it\nback.\nA constructive feature was\nthe strength of Standard Oil.t.\nLOCAL CLEARINGS\nClrinzs todas\nWNK aso\nI-ar aFo\n$3 994 120 de\n3.168.384.39\nSuuda;\nToday\u2019s New York Stocks\nINDUSTRIALS\u2014\nHigh Low\nAllied Chem\nAmerican Can\nAmerican Ice\nAmer T T....\nAmer Wool\nCent Leath\nCons Gas\nCoca Cola\nEnd-Johnson\nFreeport Texas.\nGen Asphalt\nHousehold Prod.\nInter Paper\nMay Stores\nOwen Bottle\nParish-Bing\nSeart Roe\nSterling Prod\nU S R Stores...\nWest Union\nRAILROAD\u2014\nAtchison\n64'2\n991\n85\n64\nClose\n64%\n123'2 123\n97% 977s\n84% 84%\n74\u20192\n14\n61\n74\n64%\n11\n30 12\n33%\n295\n84\n43\n10%\n815\n591\n45\n1231\n73% 73%\n13\u2019\n13\u2018\n62% 631\n73% 74\n64\n10%\n28%\n32%\n29%\n83\n42%\n10%\n81\n59\n44\n1123 109\n64%\n10%\n30%\n33%\n29%\n83\n43\n10%\n81%\n59\n44\nill\n9712\n97\nAtlant Coast.... 11312 112'\nB. 0.\nCan. Pac...\nC. 0.\nC. N. W..\nErie\nGt. Nor. Pf\n58%\n147\n73 7k\n61%\n15\n57\n60%\n57%\n14%\n72%\n60%\n14%\n55\n601,\n97%\n113*\n58\n147s\n72%\n61%\n14?;\n56%\n60%\nLehigh Valley...\nN. Y. Cen. 101% 100% 100%\nNew Haven\nNor. Pac...\nPennsy\nPere Marq.\nReading\nSouthern\nSou. Pac.\nSt. Paul.\nUnion Pac..\nWabash Pf.\n12%\n54\n41%\n411b\n77%\n35%\n87%\n13%\n12\n52%\n41%\n41\u20192\n76\n34%\n86%\n13%\n12%\n54\n41%\n41%\n76%\n35%\n87%\n13%\n130% 129% 130\u2018s\n33%\n32%\nEQUIPMENT\u2014\nAm. Loco.\n713s\n71 >2\nBaldwin\nGen. Elec.\nLima Loco.\nPullman.\nWestingh. Elec.\nons\u2014\nCal. Pete.\nCosden\nHouston.\nInvincible\nMarland.\n123\n185\ni\n65%\n122% 123%\n1807s 182%\n65\n65\n1171 1163 1163\n59%\n19 12\n21%\n48'\u00bb\n77\n21%\n691\u00bb\n19\n23%\n47\n59%\n19\n24%\n48 12\n77\n21%\n26%>\nPacific\nPan. Am. A.\nPan. Am. B.\nPhillips\nProd. Ref.\nPure Oil\nRoyal Dutch\nSinclair\nSkelly.\nStand, of Cal.\nStand, of N. J..\nTexas Co.\nMINING\u2014\nButte C Q.\nTex G S.\nMOTORS\u2014\nAm Bosch.\nChandler.\nGen Motors.\nHudson.\nMaxwell A.\nMaxwell B.\nStromberg.\nStudebaker\nStew Warner....\nTimken\nCOPPERS\u2014\nAm Smelting..\nAnaconda\nChi