118, All Fair 113, Belle Artiste 87,\nGrav\n_.. Gables 125,\nRhinegold\n110,\n\u2019Bendito 102,\n\u2019Rejection\n110,\n\u2019Omega 90, \u2019Majority 105, Snow\nMaiden 95, \u2019Leaside 111, *Glentilt\n113.\nFIFTH\u2014Claiming handicap, $1500,\n3-year-olds and up, 6 furlongs: Last\nReveille 102, Pietrus 113, Round\nRobin 107, Capt. Costigan 107, Saga\nmore 112, Joseph Brant 104, Cum\nSalt 113, Raes 108, Rock Bottom 105,\nMacduff 103, Bucado 110, Rosa Yeta\n105, Turbulent 97, *Poe 105, \u2019Mabel\nK. 96, \u2019Whalebone 105, \u2019Wraith 97.\nSIXTH\u2014The\nBowie\nhandicap,\n$10,000 added, 3-year-olds and up.\nmile and one-half: My Dear\n118,\nChacolet 112, \u2019\u2019Homestretch ill,\nExodus 111, Maximac 111, Hephais\ntos 108, aDunlin 114, aDan IV 114,\nHigh Prince 103.\n**Three pounds\npenalty included. aJ. S. Cosden en\ntry.\nSEVENTH\u20143-years olds and up,\nclaiming. $1500, mile and furlong:\nSylvan Spring 101. Old. Times 101,\n\u2019Anaprisa 103, \u2019Sling 102, Fitzrue\n108, Dellahm 110, Lady Lillian 107,\nSimoon 109, St. Donard 113, \u2019Guelph\n108, Trevelyan\n112,\nBelphrizonia\n106, \u2019Owasco 96, \u2019War Mask 10S,\nDartmoor 113, \u2018Blarnev Stone 118,\nOld Fithful 110.\n\u2019Apprentice allowance claimed.\nWeather rainy; track heavy.\nBIG PROFITS FOR\nTHE STEEL TRUST\nEarnings For Recent 3 Months\nUp Nearly 100 Per Cent\nThe steel trust has just reported\nits most profitable three months\u2019\naccording to reports to the\nbusines\nTreasury P'epartment.\nSteel profits, however, may be\nsomewhat oi a burden, political and\neconomic, the reports also indicate.\nHigh steel prices have forced the\ncost of farm implements up to the\ni point where the farmers cannot buy.\nThe farm implement business is not\ngoing to report any record-breaking\nprosperity.\nThe United States Steel corpora\ntion had total earning? during the\nthree months ending Sept. 30 of\n$37,053,680, as compared with $27,\n468,339 in the same three months\ni of last year.\nI\nThe net income of the trust was\n$33,925,911 in the three months of\nI this year, as compared with $16,\ni 297,394 in the three months of 1922.\nJudge Elbert H. Gary, head of the\ntrust, has announced extra cash divi\ndende already and the foundation is\nbeing built for more stock dividends.\nGovernment experts say an inves\ntigation will prove that the tariff\ngranted the steel industry is respon\nsible for high prices and tremendous\nprofits.\nLOCAL STOCKS\nSALKS\nBonds\n$3000 Wash R and E 49\n2300 Wash. R an 4 E 4s\n100 Pot\nE. G. and Ref tis 53\n70\nt9\u2018\n1000 Put. E G. and Ref 7s..\nStocks\n5 Continental Trust Co.\n30 Wash H. and E. pfd...\n10 Wash. Gas Light Co\nCall money\u201452.\nThe exhange will be close tomorrow\n101\n85\n7114\nIS\n1\nCHICAGO GRAIN\nWheat\nMay\nJuly\nDec.\nMay\nJuly\nOats\nDec.\nMay\nJuly\nTo.\nIL\n107%\n74%\n73\n73%\n48\nIt\n43%\nHigh\n1071,\n11'2\n107%\n7 1%\n73%\n74%\n42\n4 4%\n43%\nClose\n10.14 106'\n1107. 111'4\n100% 107%\n73%\n72%\n73%\n41%\n43%\n43 2\n74%\n73%\n73%\n41%\n1114\n13%\n1\nDe,\n$167,000 IN JEWISH DRIVE\nWith $34,740 reported at a meet\ning of team general? in the Arling\nton hotel last night, a total of $167,\n000 has been reached in the $250,\n000 Jewish Community Center drive.\nNew York Curb\nINDUSTRIALS\u2014\nHigh\nAm Gas El new 43%\nBrook\u2019n City Ry 11%\nLow\nClose\nDL&W Coal..\n94\n43% 43%\n11% 11%\nFord Mot of Can 400\nGill Safety Raz. 250\nGlen Alden Coal\nGoodyear Tire\nInercon Rubber..\nMesabi Iron.\nN J Zinc.\n79\n8 *8\n3\u20194\n5\n94\n400\n246\n76%\n8%\n3%\n5\n94\n400\n250\n78%\n8%\n3%\n5\n1397s 139% 139%\nN Y Tel pfd.... 109% 109% 109%\nRadio\nSouth C Iron.\nSwift Co.\nTob Prod Exp...\nU S Lt Ht pfd.\nU Ret Candy A.\nWayne Coal.\nWil Cor 1st pfd.\n3%\n17\n3%\n15\n3\u20194\n16\n101% 10112 10112\n412\n80\n5%\n1\n6\n412\n80\n5%\n1\n6\n416\n80\n5%\n1\n6\nINDEPENDENT OILS\nArk Nat Gas....\nCities Service 130\n4%\nMarland Mex\nMexico Oil\nMount. Prod.\nMut. Oil, vtc...\nRoyal Can. Oil..\nSalt Creek Prod.\nSea. O. and G...\nSo. States Oil..\n23\n40\n14\n4%\n129\n2%\n20\n13%\n103s 10 4a\n3%\n18% 18\n35,\n80\n15%\nSTANDARD OIL\u2014\n10\n15%\n4%\n130\n2%\n30\n13%\n10%\n35s\n18\n77\n15%\nAng. Amer. Oil.\nBuckeye Pipe L.\n1412\n73\n1414\nCumb. Pipe Line 114\nImp. Oil of Can..\nInt. Pet.\nOhio Oil\n96\n151\n57\n114\n95%\n15\n56%\nPr. O. and G.. 184le 182\nPr. Pipe Linet\nSt. O. of Inti..\nSt. O. of N. Y..\nVacuum Oil\n98\n97\n56% 5512\n4132403\n52\n51\n14%\n73\n114\n95%\n15\n57\n183 12\n9712\n55%\n41\nLIBERTY BONDS\nBy Redmond Co.\nAll fractious are in thirty seconds._\n_Issue _1O pen Hizh Low Close\n0910 9919 9i 18 95 Mi\n3e8\nlat 11,8.\n2d\nd\nUh i,s\n32\nOS 01 0% 97.31 98 O'\n1 O'\n5 07\n07 24 07 H\n18.29: 00.00 00 28 00 31\n0'\ni 99.0.\n8 OH 01 07 8 07 31\n00.10 00 OH !<0 10\nFOREIGN EXCHANGE\nDemand\nEngland, pound.\nGermrany,\nSI\nFrance, franc\nItaly, lira.\nCan da dollar.\nSweden, krone..\nJapan, yen\n1\nH4i\n23\nUl\n19\n00\n24\n19\n1 1 t 375\n00000000003\n3 70\n4 46\n15 pc dist\nt 33\n8.63\nMER ROUGE REIGN\nOF TERROR AIRED\nBy United Press\nBASTROP, La.\u2014Louisiana\u2019s third\nattempt to bring to justice alleged\nparticipants in the Morehouse parish\nreign of terror, which culminated in\nthe murder of Watt Daniel and\nThomas F. Richardson Aug. 24, 1922,\ngot under way here today.\nDistrict Judge Odom called to the\nbar a score of defendants charged\nwith misdemeanors\nin connection\nwith mob activities on occasions\nother than the double murder.\nThe state plans thus to build a\ngroundwork for\nmore\nimportant\ncases, such as that of Capt. J. K.\nSkipwith, local Klan official.\nThe bodies of Daniel and Richards\nwere\ntaken from Lake Lafourche\nlast December.\nTO PLAN IMPROVEMENTS\nBell Will Outline Five Years' Needs\nof City\nCommissioner Bell'and his assis\ntant, Capt. John E. Wood, will pre\npare a five-year\nprogram of the\ncity\u2019s needs to ba followed in mak\ning the annual estimates.\nIncluded in the program will be\nthe water, sewer, and highway de\npartment needs.\nPRINCELY HACKER A WIT\nPARIS\u2014Mme. Iswolsky, widow of\nthe Russian ambassador to Paris,\nwas waiting for a taxi in the Rue\nRoyale the other day.\nOne came along.\ncried.\n\u201cWhat!\u201d she\n\u201cYou, Prince Christoforis,\nyou driving a taxi.\nWhen I knew\nyou in Petersburg you had a dozen\ncarriages!\u201d\n\u201cYes,\nMadame,\u201d\nretorted\nthe\nprincely chauffeur. \u201cI\u2019m driving a\ntaxi, but I don\u2019t ride in one.\u201d\nCAN\u2019T EXAMINE BOOKS\nJustice Robb today found that the\nrequest of Eugene Wharton for a\nmandamus against Albert W. How\nard, secretary of the Fireman\u2019s In\nsurance Co. for an inspection of the\ncompany\u2019s stock book, was for \"an\nulterior purpose, to harrass, and\nperhaps to destroy the corporation.\u201d\nJustice Robb upheld decision of Dis\ntrict supreme court in refusing the\naction.\nSTANDARD OILS\nLEAD CURB GAIN\nMarket Picks Up in Afternoon\nAfter Early Heaviness\nBy United Financial\nNEW YORK\u2014After heavine\nPy.\ntending into the early afternoon, the\ncurb market showed a better tend,\nency under the influence of some f\nthe Standard Oil leaders.\nIndiana\ndeclared its regular quarterly 622c\ndividend and the forward movenent\nof petroleums on the \"big boata\nfound its reflection on the curb.\nacuum is Active\nI Vacuus was active at 51% in tie\nafternoon and reached 52, up 3.\ni After a period of weakness. Prairie\ni Oil Gas recovered to 184, up 1.\nOhio was up 12. In the indepe\nwitiv **ee> up \u00bb\u00abi jnur\ndents. Mutual and Gulf States\nOil\nwere at the best prices of last\nweek\u2019s close. Humble and Standard\nof New York were weaker.\nMex Fuel on one sale picked\nnearly a point.\nPen:\nP\nGillette, which did not sell until\n1 o\u2019clock, enjoyed a period of actr.\nity within a range of 4 points, open\ning at 247, compared with the clo e\nat 248, slipping back a point a\ntional, then advancing sharp! j y\n250. Glen Alden Coal was able to\ncontinue its advance around\nBorden Co. moved up \u2019a to 120-,\nD. L. W. Coal a point to 94.\nAmerican Gas at New High\nAmerican Gas Electric, whic\nhas been strong in sympathy with\nelectric bond and share a group on\nthe counter market, established\nnew 1923 high at 43%.\nDublier Radio Condenser wa.\nbetter. Profit-taking in Park T\nford carried this issue down over a\nponit to 33'4. Chicago Nipple \u201cA\"\nnew was easier.\nRenewed weakness made its ap\npearance in Cleveland Motors an!\nthe price tapered off St to 2214. Me\nCrory new appeared at 80, off\nIn the metals, New Jersey Zinc n\ni peated its last week\u2019s\n139\u2018s.\nest level.\n\ni\nI\nFIVE HELD IN DRY RAID\nFive men were arrested and a 200\ngallon still and 20 barrels of ma\nwere seized yesterday in a raid near\nMarshall Hall, Md., led by Prohih:\ntion Agent Linton S. Evans, Balti\nmore.\nWilliam Hull, said to be the ope\nator of the still, anti-four other\ni prisoners were taken.\nDR. M\u2019COY TO SPEAK\nDr. George W. McCoy, director\nthe Hygenic laboratory, will speak\nat the Wapiya club luncheon, at th\nUniversity club, Wednesday at 12:4\np. m.\nI\nYOUR DOLLAR\n1\nUncle Sam Tells Who\nGets It\nT\n4\ni\n\n\nt\ni\n1\nI\n1\nBREAKFAST FOODS\n\ni\ni\n74+\nCents\ni\ni\ni\nHate\nials\n20\n6Cenrs\nCenis\nProfr\nOverhead\nTaxes\n\nCOPR.onT 01 RAPn P.CDUM,Wac\nMANUFACTURERS of breakfa.i\nfood in the United States in a\nyear receive about $1.50 for every\nperson in the country. The greater\npart of what they receive goes t.\npay for their materials.\nAccording to information gathere\nby the government 74 cents out o'\neach dollar the breakfast-food man\nufacturer receives represents the co\nof his material. Six cents pays hi:\nlabor, leaving him 20 cents to pa.\nhis own profit, overhead and taxes.\nA 16 per cent increase in wage\nwould increase the selling price ne\nquite 1 cent on each dollar\u2014ninet)\nsix one-hundredths of a cent is th'\nexact figure. A 16 per cent increas\nin the cost of materials would ad\nnearly 12 cents on each one dollar.\nNext Issue\u2014Lace.","height":"21680","width":"14276"}}
